I got a question. If one of your own family pass on  how to stay strong.
Time heal. Been thru that ..
the hole in your heart just gets smaller over time
Right now I just feel like I not use to be alone
depends a lot on what role they used to play in your life... it will help if you have other people around to help you keep busy
She is my only parent left. Basically without her I all alone

not to bury your emotions of grief and sadness  maybe anger and bitterness  but to acknowledge and help redirect your brooding away from what is destructive and unhelpful to you as someone your family / relative loved.
So the best is to keep myself busy
a large part of it  but you also still need time to acknowledge and deal with the missing parts of your emotions / life / relations
Thank for the advice. I try my best to go through it

know that you're not alone in this world  seek close friends and other relatives who may be similarly hurting. no one will hurt like you do  but also  you will not hurt like they do. it is important not to deny the pain and grief.. but also to not deny others' sense of loss
